Set Up Your Org for the Adoption Analytics App

Before creating an app from the Adoption Analytics template, configure your org to collect necessary data. The app collects logs that track how often users open CRM Analytics apps, dashboards, and lenses. If you have the CRM Analytics Plus or CRM Analytics Growth license, your app includes Analytics log data. Your app includes Event Monitoring bundle data if you also have the Event Monitoring license.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition. All app users have a CRM Analytics Plus or CRM Analytics Growth license.


USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create and manage the Adoption Analytics app:	
Access Adoption Analytics Templates and Apps
Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps


To use the Adoption Analytics app:	
Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Event, and then select Event Monitoring Settings.
Turn on View event log data in analytics apps and Generate event log files.
In the Quick Find box, enter Analytics, and then select Settings.
Select Extract Adoption Analytics Metadata via Dataflow.
Save your changes.
title: Configuring Salesforce for Adoption Analytics App
